Foreign nationals are currently allowed to leave Armenia on regular commercial flights, though the majority of airlines have suspended routes. If you wish to depart Armenia, you should aim to do so while commercial options remain open. Contact carriers directly for the latest information and guidance.
On 24 February the Armenian authorities announced that the Meghri border crossing with Iran would be closed and scheduled flights between Armenia and Iran would be suspended, other than for Armenian and Iranian citizens to be returned to their respective countries.
With effect from 14 March, the borders between Armenia and Georgia will be closed for the movement of people, other than for the return of the citizens of each country to their country of origin. This does not apply to the movement of goods.
